# ERP Executive Ledger Output Template Standard

## Phase

BRANDING.5 — Executive Ledger Template Engine (2026-07-02)

---

## Rule 1 — All formal ERP print/PDF output MUST use the Executive Ledger engine

Any new or refactored module producing formal, official documents for print or PDF
MUST use `renderExecutiveLedgerHtml()` via an `ExecutiveLedgerDocument` definition.

Applicable document types: HR letters, salary certificates, NOCs, PPE forms, clearance forms,
purchase orders, delivery notes, weighbridge tickets, certificates, official company forms.

**Library location:**
```
src/lib/executive-ledger/
src/features/executive-ledger/
```

---

## Rule 2 — Build ExecutiveLedgerDocument from pre-formatted data

Never pass raw database rows or server types to the renderer.

### Correct pattern

```tsx
import { elColumnLabel, elFormatValue, elFormatDate } from "@/lib/executive-ledger/formatters";
import type { ExecutiveLedgerDocument } from "@/lib/executive-ledger/types";

const doc: ExecutiveLedgerDocument = {
  documentTitle: "Experience Letter",
  issuedDate: elFormatDate(new Date().toISOString()),
  branding: resolvedBranding, // ExportBrandingContext from server
  sections: [
    {
      type: "key_value",
      title: "Employee Details",
      rows: [
        { label: "Full Name", value: elFormatValue(employee.full_name_en) },
        { label: "Date of Joining", value: elFormatDate(employee.joining_date) },
      ],
    },
  ],
};
```

### Forbidden pattern

```tsx
// ❌ NEVER — raw row data, raw dates, no formatting
const doc: ExecutiveLedgerDocument = {
  documentTitle: "Experience Letter",
  sections: [{
    type: "key_value",
    rows: [
      { label: "Name", value: employee.full_name_en }, // ← might be null
      { label: "Date", value: employee.joining_date }, // ← raw ISO string
    ],
  }],
};
```

---

## Rule 3 — Never resolve branding inside the renderer

The renderer (`renderExecutiveLedgerHtml`) is a pure function.
It never calls Supabase, never generates signed URLs, and never calls any server action.

Pass pre-resolved `ExportBrandingContext` from the server (BRANDING.4 `resolveTemplatePreview()`).

```tsx
// ✓ Correct — branding passed from server action
const branding = await resolveTemplatePreview(templateId);
const doc: ExecutiveLedgerDocument = { ..., branding };

// ❌ Wrong — calling Supabase from inside render context
// const logoUrl = await supabase.storage.createSignedUrl(...)  ← FORBIDDEN
```

---

## Rule 4 — Stamp and signature are gated by reports.sign

Stamp and signature URLs are only present in `ExportBrandingContext` when the requesting user
has the `reports.sign` permission (enforced by BRANDING.4 server actions).

The renderer renders them only when the URLs are non-empty. Do not bypass this gate.

```tsx
// ✓ Renderer checks: stampUrl is only non-null when user has reports.sign
// ✓ No need to re-check permission in the renderer
```

---

## Rule 5 — Always escape dynamic values

All text injected into the HTML output MUST go through `elEscapeHtml()`.
All URL attributes MUST go through `elEscapeAttr()` (validates https:// only).

These are already enforced inside `renderExecutiveLedgerHtml()` for all built-in fields.
If you add custom HTML-building functions alongside the renderer, you MUST use them too.

---

## Rule 6 — Preview MUST use the iframe component

When previewing Executive Ledger output in React, always use `ExecutiveLedgerPreview`
which renders inside an `<iframe srcdoc="">` for isolation.

```tsx
// ✓ Correct
import { ExecutiveLedgerPreview } from "@/features/executive-ledger";
<ExecutiveLedgerPreview document={doc} height={600} />

// ❌ Wrong — dangerouslySetInnerHTML bypasses iframe isolation
<div dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: renderExecutiveLedgerHtml(doc) }} />
```

---

## Rule 7 — QR placeholder vs QR generation

Setting `qrPlaceholder: true` in `ExecutiveLedgerDocument` renders only a visual placeholder.
It does NOT generate a QR code. QR generation is BRANDING.6.

Do NOT attempt to implement QR generation, verification tokens, or public verify endpoints
until BRANDING.6 is explicitly approved.

---

## Rule 8 — No hardcoded ALGT / company-specific values in the engine

The Executive Ledger engine is tenant-agnostic. All company identity (name, logo, colors)
comes from `ExportBrandingContext`. Never hardcode company names, colors, or logos
in `src/lib/executive-ledger/` or `src/features/executive-ledger/`.

